  "title": "Senior/ Executive, Corporate Secretarial",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>• Assist in preparing necessary documents and maintaining statutory records on all matters related to incorporation, annual compliance, and ad-hoc corporate changes for the Group.<br />• Liaise with statutory bodies, banks, and other third-party business partners, as required.<br />• Prepare and review minutes of Directors’ and Shareholders’ meetings and Directors’ and Shareholders’ resolutions for specific corporate transactions.<br />• Ensure compliance with relevant statutory and regulatory requirements, including the Singapore Companies Act and SGX Listing Rules.<br />• Assist the Group in matters relating to corporate governance and sustainability reporting.<br />• Assist with the Group’s statutory administration, including work passes, business licenses, and related matters.<br />• Handle statutory filings with ACRA in compliance with the Singapore Companies Act.<br />• Perform general corporate, administrative, and secretarial duties for the department.<br />• Organise Board and Committee meetings, Annual General Meeting and liaise with auditors.</p><p>• Administer the Employees’ Share Option Scheme (ESOS) and Performance Share Plan (PSP) related matters.</p><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><p>• Minimum of 3 years of working experience in the corporate secretarial field in Singapore.  Preference will be given to candidates with Institute of Chartered Secretaries and Administrators (ICSA).<br />• Strong knowledge of the Singapore Companies Act, SGX Listing Rules and related regulatory requirements.<br />• A good team player and able to work independently.<br />• Able to organise and prioritise work with minimum supervision.<br />• Strong interpersonal skills with excellent written and communication skills in English.</p><p>The work location will be at 25 Tannery Lane. </p><p><strong>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</strong></p>",
